formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1. The management of the real estate project is responsible for completeness and accuracy of the underlying data and complete disclosure of all material and relevant information to us and preparing and maintaining the details of booked and unbooked inventory in accordance with the applicable laws and regulations.
2. It is not possible for us to comment or express an opinion on physical progress of the project mentioned in Form-1 by project architect and cost incurred mentioned in Form-2 by project engineer as it is not within the scope of our practice and it is beyond our professional competence.
3. Information of block type, unit no., usage, carpet area, area of exclusive balcony/ verandah, unit consideration, unit-wise received amount, date of agreement to sale, encumbrance status, allotee name, type of KYC, KYC ID, mobile no., redevelopment details mentioned in Form-3 (Annexure) are taken as certified by management. Management is responsible for completeness and accuracy of the said information.
4. The information furnished in Column-A of this certificate is forecasted by the management and we are not certifying the said forecasts.
5. Mobile No. is of staff of promoter in all Units as information is not available with the promoter.
6. In Sr. No. 8 of Form-3 Net Amount which can be withdrawn from the Designated Bank Account under this certificate (Rs.) is -12544888. The reason behind this is Total Cost Incurred and Paid of the Real Estate Project (Rs.) is 69226946 as per our Form-3 but the estimated cost of construction as certified by an engineer is 44200000 and the difference is 25026946. Due to this difference, Sr. 3 in form-3 is shows 58469375 instead of 73746787. If we consider actual expenses incurred then there is no excess withdrawal.
